					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Well, if you are testing on the real NES, you won't be able to see sprites in the corner, will you?</div>
<br />In Europe you can, as European TVs have more visible scanlines. The NES image is always 240 scanlines tall, but an image 240 scanlines tall on a PAL TV is as tall as something 200 scanlines tall on an NTSC or PAL60 TV: easily within the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Safe_area" class="postlink">safe area</a>.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

