				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Most commercial NES games were devlopped assuming that the top and bottom 8 pixels are not visible to the user, causing graphical glitches in PAL.
<br />For this reason, I think have emulator hide top and bottom borders is a good thing, even if it doesn't really emulate the hardware, blah, blah, blah, it is looking what most games were designed for.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
